Problem 1

Create a dataframe containing: the names of the players, the minutes played, and their three-point shooting percentage. How many players are in the roster for 2024?

wnba_page <- read_html('https://www.basketball-reference.com/wnba/years/2024_totals.html')



wnba_data <- data.frame(
  'name' = wnba_page |>
  html_elements('th.left') |>
  html_text(trim = TRUE),
  
  'minutes' = wnba_page |>
  html_elements('.right:nth-child(5)') |>
  html_text(trim = TRUE) |>
  as.numeric(),
  
  'three_percentage' = wnba_page |>
  html_elements('.right:nth-child(14)') |>
  html_text(trim = TRUE) |>
  as.numeric()
  
)

Question 2

Create a graph of the distribution of the three-point shooting percentage made by each players. Report and interpret appropriate statistics.

hist(wnba_data$three_percentage, main = "Distribution of three point shooting percentage", xlab = "Percentage (%)", col = "lightblue")

mean(wnba_data$three_percentage, na.rm = TRUE)
## [1] 0.2971173
median(wnba_data$three_percentage, na.rm = TRUE)
## [1] 0.3155

The mean is around 0.297 and the median is around 0.316. Players have a three-point shooting percentage of about 29.7%. This indicates a slight left or negative skew because the mean is less than the median.

Question 3

Create a graph that shows the relationship between the minutes played by each player and their three-point shooting percentage. Choose one particular player, highlight her point on the graph and label it with her name.

ggplot(wnba_data, aes(x = minutes, y = three_percentage)) +
  geom_point(color = "blue", size = 2) +
  labs(
    title = "Relationship Between Minutes Played and Three-Point Shooting Percentage",
    x = "Minutes Played",
    y = "Three-Point Shooting Percentage (%)"
  ) +
  theme_minimal()
## Warning: Removed 21 rows containing missing values or values outside the scale range
## (`geom_point()`).

caitlin_clark <- wnba_data[wnba_data$name == "Caitlin Clark", ]


ggplot(wnba_data, aes(x = minutes, y = three_percentage)) +
  geom_point(color = "blue", size = 2) + 
  geom_point(data = caitlin_clark, aes(x = minutes, y = three_percentage), color = "red", size = 3) +  
  geom_text(data = caitlin_clark, aes(x = minutes, y = three_percentage, label = name), color = "red") + 
  labs(
    title = "Relationship Between Minutes Played and Three-Point Shooting Percentage",
    x = "Minutes Played",
    y = "3 Point Shooting Percentage (%)"
  ) +
  theme_minimal()
## Warning: Removed 21 rows containing missing values or values outside the scale range

The player Caitlin Clark is highlighted in red showing her 3 point shooting percentage.
